 perspectives on gender using their own personal experiences of understanding and negotiating Western and Asian identities and practices. The book paves the way for important reflections about the ontological and epistemological meanings of ‘Asia’, ‘gender’ and ‘tourism’. It is an important resource for researchers from a range of disciplines including tourism, leisure studies, Asian studies and feminist and gender studies, as well as for professionals working in the tourism industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAsiansxEthnic identity. 0aSex rolezAsia. 0aTourismxSocial aspectszAsia. 4aBlack & Asian studies. 4aGender studies, gender groups. 4aTourism industry. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Hospitality, Travel & Tourism.2bisacsh  aAsia.  aAsian identities.  aAsian.  aFemininity.  aGender issues.  aGender studies.  aGender.  aMasculinity.  aTourism.1 aBadruddoja, Roksana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBakar, Barkathunnisha Abu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhoo-Lattimore, Catheryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhoo-Lattimore, Catheryn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLim, Tau Sian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMura, Paolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMura, Paolo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRawat, Karun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTan, Eunice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTavakoli, Rokhshad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYang, Elaine Chiao Ling, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/